-- South Africa’s Malema Says Won’t Leave ANC Party, SAPA Reports
-- B y   A n d r e s   R .   M a r t i n e z
-- 2012-03-03T13:15:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-03/south-africa-s-malema-says-won-t-leave-anc-party-sapa-reports.html
African National Congress Youth
League President  Julius Malema  won’t leave the ruling party
after its disciplinary committee expelled him this week, the
South African Press Association reported.  Malema told the ANC’s Women’s League in Limpopo province
today that he will “die in this movement,” the Johannesburg-
based  news agency  reported.  Malema has 14 days to appeal his removal from the party.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andres R. Martinez in Johannesburg at 
 amartinez28@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
